questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a Spring-based web application deployed on Apache Tomcat suffers from a gradual heap memory leak under high load, eventually leading to `OutOfMemoryError`. Profiling indicates that millions of `byte[]` arrays are retained. A code review reveals the following class:

java
@Component
@Scope("prototype")
public class RequestContextProcessor {
    private static final ThreadLocal<byte[]> processingBuffer = ThreadLocal.withInitial(() -> new byte[1024 * 1024]); // 1MB buffer

    @Transactional
    public void processRequest(InputStream input) {
        byte[] buffer = processingBuffer.get();
        // Read input into buffer and process...
        // No explicit cleanup is performed
    }
}
